{{more citations needed|date=June 2017}} {{Infobox prepared food | name = Broyé Poitevin | image = File:Broye du Poitou.jpg | caption = Broyé du Poitou | image_alt = Broyé du Poitou | alternate_name = Broyé du Poitou | country = [[France]] | region = [[Nouvelle-Aquitaine]] | creator = | course = | type = [[Cake]] | served = | main_ingredient = [[sugar]], [[flour]], [[butter]] and [[Egg (food)|eggs]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Broyé du Poitou|url=http://www.marmiton.org/recettes/recette_broye-du-poitou_11696.aspx|website=Marmiton.org|accessdate=14 June 2017|language=French}}</ref> | variations = | calories = | other = }} The '''broyé poitevin''' or '''broyé du Poitou''' is a [[cake]] from the [[Nouvelle-Aquitaine]] region of [[France]] and made of [[sugar]], [[flour]], [[butter]] and [[Egg (food)|eggs]].
It is available in large or small sizes (8–100&nbsp;cm in diameter and about 2&nbsp;cm thick).
== Confrérie de l'Ordre des Chevaliers de la Grand Goule == Founded in 2004 in [[Poitiers]], the [[Confrérie de l'Ordre des Chevaliers de la Grand Goule]] promotes the broyé poitevin. Its objective is to protect and enhance the tradition of the broyé poitevin. The Confrérie organises the annual Rencontres Gourmandes du Poitou.
