'''Ghazni Airport''' ({{lang-ps|د غزني هوايي ډګر}}; {{airport codes|GZI|OAGN|p=n}}) is located in [[Ghazni]], Afghanistan, next to the main [[Kabul–Kandahar Highway|Ghazni-Kandahar Highway]].<ref>http://goo.gl/maps/1IgrN</ref> It serves the population of [[Ghazni Province|Ghazni]] and other nearby [[Provinces of Afghanistan|Afghan provinces]]. The airport is mainly used for civilian flights and is still being developed as of late 2013.<ref name=PAN>{{cite news | url = http://www.pajhwok.com/en/2013/12/28/7m-ghazni-civil-airport-inaugurated | title = $7m Ghazni civil airport inaugurated | publisher = [[Pajhwok Afghan News]] | date = 28 December 2013|accessdate = 28 December 2013|first = Saifullah |last = Maftoon }}</ref>
==History== It was formerly a [[military airfield]] until the [[Politics of Afghanistan|Afghan government]] recently decided to turn it into an international airport. It currently has one [[runway]] designated 15/33 with a length of {{convert|1000|ft|0}}.<ref name="MOTCA" />
The government plans to add two runways in the near future. The overall project is expected to be completed in 2014.<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.pajhwok.com/en/2013/07/02/work-ghazni-airport-launched | title = Work on Ghazni airport launched | publisher = Pajhwok Afghan News | date = 2 July 2013|accessdate = 5 July 2013|first = Saifullah |last = Maftoon }}</ref> The first phase of the project was inaugurated in late December 2013 after a smaller private aircraft landed at the runway of Ghazni Airport.<ref name=PAN/>
