'''TCG ''Büyükada'' (F-512)''' is the second ship of the {{sclass2-|Ada|corvette|0}} [[anti-submarine warfare|ASW]] [[corvette]]s of the [[Turkish Navy]]. TCG ''Büyükada'' was named after [[Büyükada|Büyükada Island]]. Büyükada Island is part of the [[Prince Islands]] [[archipelago]] in the [[Sea of Marmara]], to the southeast of [[Istanbul]]. Its [[sister ship]] is {{TCG|Heybeliada|F-511|6}}.
Designed, developed and built by the Tuzla (Istanbul) Naval Shipyard as a part of the [[MILGEM project]], it was [[Keel laying|laid down]] on 22 January 2008, [[Ceremonial ship launching|launched]] on 27 September 2011, and [[Ship commissioning|commissioned]] on 27 September 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dzkk.tsk.tr/turkce/MODERNIZASYON.php?strAnaFrame=modernizasyon&strIFrame=MilgemProjesi |publisher=Deniz Kuvvetleri Komutanlığı |title=Milli Olarak Dizayn ve İmşa Edilen İlk Türk Korveti MİLGEM Projesi |language=Turkish |accessdate=2013-09-27 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.denizhaber.com.tr/dzkk-sgk/51326/tcg-buyukada-dzkkya-teslim-edildi-denizhaber-istanbul-tersanesi-gemi-buyukada-ba.html |newspaper=Deniz Haber |title=TCG Büyükada, DZKK'ya teslim edildi |date=2013-09-27 |language=Turkish |accessdate=2013-09-27 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/gundem/24805939.asp |newspaper=[[Hürriyet]] |title=2. hayalet gemi denizde |author=Küçük, Mustafa |date=2013-09-28 |language=Turkish |accessdate=2013-09-28 }}</ref>
== History == In 2015, she completed a three-month voyage, visiting ports in Saudi Arabia, Yemen, Pakistan, Qatar, Kuwait, Bahrain, Sudan and Djibouti.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.denizhaber.com.tr/milli-gururumuz-tcg-buyukada-yurda-dondu-haber-61486.htm|title=Milli gururumuz TCG Büyükada yurda döndü|website=Deniz Haber|access-date=2016-04-27}}</ref> She was involved in the successful evacuation of 55 Turkish citizens from Yemen.<ref name=":0" />
